<para id="fs-id1164564452632">Suppose you computed <emphasis effect="italics">r</emphasis> = 0.776 and <emphasis effect="italics">n</emphasis> = 6, with <emphasis effect="italics">df</emphasis> = 6 - 2 = 4. The critical values are  0.811 and 0.811. Since 0.776 is between the two critical values, <emphasis effect="italics">r</emphasis> is not significant. The line should not be used for prediction.</para><figure id="linrgs_facts5"><media id="id1165447912701" alt="Horizontal number line with values -0.924, -0.532, and 0.532."><image src="../../media/fig-ch12_07_03.jpg" mime-type="image/jpeg" width="380"/></media><caption>–0.811 &lt; <emphasis effect="italics">r</emphasis> = 0.776 &lt; 0.811. Therefore, <emphasis effect="italics">r</emphasis> is not significant.</caption>
</figure>
</example>

