<section id="fs-idm89842304"><title>Third Exam vs. Final Exam Example: Critical Value Method</title><para id="eip-666">Consider the <link document="m79689" target-id="element-22">third exam/final exam example</link>.
The line of best fit is: <emphasis effect="italics">ŷ</emphasis> = –173.51 + 4.83<emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>, with <emphasis effect="italics">r</emphasis> = .6631, and there are <emphasis effect="italics">n</emphasis> = 11 data points. Can the regression line be used for prediction? Given a third exam score (<emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis> value), can we use the line to predict the final exam score (predicted <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis> value)?
</para><list id="eip-830" list-type="labeled-item"><item><emphasis effect="italics">H</emphasis><sub>0</sub>: <emphasis effect="italics">ρ</emphasis> = 0</item>
<item> <emphasis effect="italics">H<sub>a</sub></emphasis>: <emphasis effect="italics">ρ</emphasis> ≠ 0 </item>
<item><emphasis effect="italics">α</emphasis> = 0.05</item>
</list><list id="eip-557" list-type="bulleted" bullet-style="bullet"><item>Use the 95 Percent Critical Values table for <emphasis effect="italics">r</emphasis> with <emphasis effect="italics">df</emphasis> = <emphasis effect="italics">n</emphasis> – 2 = 11 – 2 = 9.</item>
<item>Using the table with <emphasis effect="italics">df</emphasis> = 9, we find that the critical value listed is 0.602. Therefore, the critical values are ±0.602.</item>
<item>Since 0.6631 &gt; 0.602, <emphasis effect="italics">r</emphasis> is significant.</item>
<item>Decision: Reject the null hypothesis.</item>
<item>Conclusion: There is sufficient evidence to conclude there is a significant  linear relationship between the third exam score (<emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>) and the final exam score (<emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>) because the correlation coefficient is significantly different from zero.</item>
</list><para id="eip-138">Because <emphasis effect="italics">r</emphasis> is significant and the scatter plot shows a linear trend, the regression line can be used to predict final exam scores.</para>

